  "footnotes": [
    "Baqt Treaty (652 CE): Agreement between Arab Egypt (Umayyad) and Christian Makuria; required Makuria to supply slaves annually in exchange for goods; unusual in that it guaranteed Makuria's independence; lasted roughly 600 years.",
    "Nobatia/Makuria/Alwa: Three Christian Nubian kingdoms that emerged after the fall of Meroe; all converted to Miaphysite Christianity (c.540–580 CE); Makuria and Nobatia merged (c.700); Alwa survived independently until c.1504.",
    "Funj Sultanate (Sennar, 1504–1821): Founded when Funj people allied with Abdallah Jamma (Arab leader) to defeat Alwa; capital at Sennar on the Blue Nile; the Funj (Black Sultanate) ruled until Egyptian conquest.",
    "Mahdist State (1881–1898): Founded by Muhammad Ahmad ibn Abd Allah, who declared himself the Mahdi (guided one); his forces killed General Gordon in Khartoum (1885); destroyed by Kitchener at the Battle of Omdurman (1898).",
    "Darfur conflict (2003–): Rebellion by non-Arab groups against the Arab-dominated Khartoum government; counter-insurgency by Janjaweed militias; ICC indicted President Bashir for genocide.",
    "South Sudan independence (2011): Following the Comprehensive Peace Agreement (2005) ending the second Sudanese civil war, a referendum produced a 98.83% vote for independence; became the world's newest country on 9 July 2011.",
    "Sudan civil war (2023–): Fighting broke out between the Sudanese Armed Forces (SAF) and the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) paramilitary in April 2023; one of the world's worst humanitarian crises by 2024."
  ]
